Error: Error: "Unable To Allocate X MB Of RAM: Java.Lang.OutOfMemoryError:"

This Error Occurs When The Minecraft Server Is Unable To Allocate Enough Memory From The System For Its Operation. It Is Commonly Encountered When Trying To Allocate More Memory Than What The System Can Provide.

Solution: 1. Login to your Pterodactyl Panel and navigate to the server you're experiencing this issue with.
2. Click on "Console" to open the console of the Minecraft server.
3. Stop
